						               													<description>HE WHO DIES WITH THE MOST LOOT&amp;#10;NOW PROBABLY FOUND THE STAIRS&amp;#10;DOWN TO THE 2nd LEVEL&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first expansion for Loot and Scoot adds new monsters, new treasures, new adventurers, new buildings and the official solitaire rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;With this expansion, you can build Fountains of Healing, Statues of Glory (with a value based on how well you can loot the dungeon) and even own a Tavern. Dual-class characters, like Paladins and Rangers, can be hired at the Inn. Secret Rooms are waiting to be discovered, hiding incredible powerful magical weapons (loot a +1 Dagger or Wand of Magic +1!). New traps are available to hinder (or kill) your opponents. Even the undead stir in the dungeons below.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two additional player mats are included for variety. Now every dungeon master can have their own dungeon type.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Notice: This Expansion Kit is not a &amp;lsquo;stand alone&amp;rsquo; game. To use it, you must own a copy of Loot and Scoot&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Complexity: 2 on a 9 scale&amp;#10;Solitaire Suitability: 4 on a 9 scale&amp;#10;Scale: Individual heroes vs. individual or groups of monsters&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Components:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     One illustrated, color 2-page Rules sheet&amp;#10;     40 color, die-cut 5/8&amp;quot; square playing pieces&amp;#10;     2 Dungeon player mats&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
